                                        Cap Breton, September 2005
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 4 > list 4 > element 4">
                                        Toronto, September 2011
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>
                                <li>
                                    <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 4 > list 4 > element 5">
                                        Cranbrooke, September 2012
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>
                                <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 5 > b">
                                    Most Outstanding New JCI Organization in the Americas
                                </ui:msg>
                            </b>
                            <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 5">
                                at Area Conferences
                            </ui:msg>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 6 > list 5 > element 1">
                                        Quito, Equator, May 19, 2003
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>

                                <li>
                                    <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 6 > list 5 > element 2">
                                        Sao Paulo, May 7, 2005
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <ul>
                        <li>
                            <b>
                                <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 7 > b">
                                    Most Outstanding New JCI Organization in the World
                                </ui:msg>
                            </b>
                            <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 7">
                                at World Congress
                            </ui:msg>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <ul>
                                <li>
                                    <ui:msg description="About > list 3 > element 8">
                                        Copenhagen, Denmark, Nov, 2003
                                    </ui:msg>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <p>
                    <ui:msg description="About > paragraph 13">
                        In 2004, JCI Quebec City hosted the National Convention after being part of JCI and JCI Canada for
                        only two years. Quebec City established a benchmark for conventions in Canada by offering VIP
                        treatment to all of our guests. JCI Quebec City maintains relationships with a number of external
                        organizations among local chapters and national organisations of the JCI movement.
                    </ui:msg>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <ui:msg description="About > paragraph 14">
                        JCI Quebec City
                        being the only French speaking chapter in North America, contacts were also made with other junior
                        chambers of French background. Since 2005, JCI Quebec City though JCI Canada has become a member of
                        JCI’s Association Internationale des Jeunes Chambres Francophones (International Francophone Junior
                        Chambers Association). Finally, JCI Quebec City is twinned with JCI Calgary and JCI Reims to develop
                        relations that are mutually beneficial.
                    </ui:msg>
                </p>
                <p class="{res.style.noBottomMargin}">
                    <ui:msg description="About > paragraph 9">
                        For more information, visit
                    </ui:msg>
                    <a href="http://www.jccq.qc.ca/" target="_blank">
                        <ui:msg description="About > link 2">
                            www.jccq.qc.ca
                        </ui:msg>
                    </a>.
                </p>
                <g:Image addStyleNames="{aboutRes.style.imgLogo}" resource="{aboutRes.jccq}" altText="JCCQ Logo"/>
